en_164923_0	Former President Mahinda Rajapaksa stated that the Joint Opposition will decide to refrain from presenting proposals for the new constitution until an election is held.
en_164923_1	The former president expressed these views addressing a meeting held in Monaragala yesterday.
en_164923_2	Meanwhile, the former president stated that a draft bill has been gazetted to enforce the International Convention for the Protection of All Persons from Enforced Disappearance in Sri Lanka.
en_164923_3	The former president in a communiqué notes that the draft bill will only result in the country’s war heroes being betrayed before International Criminal Courts and courts of other countries.
